 • At the time of the explosion, the blast wave destroyed or damaged nearly every building within a 1-mile (1.6 km) radius of the hypocenter, including 90% of the city of Hiroshima;
• Total deaths from the atomic bombing, including immediate deaths and deaths from radiation exposure in the months that followed, may have been between 90,000 and 140,000 people;
• The city's administrative buildings, hospitals, school buildings, and private residences were mostly destroyed;
• The blast also destroyed the city's electric power facilities, water supply systems, and sewage systems, as well as its firefighting equipment and rescue vehicles;
• The heat and pressure from the blast caused fires to break out across the city, which further destroyed buildings and caused additional injuries and deaths.
